[{"id":"FT554823","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"These two paintings take different approaches to contemporary political events. Identify the artist of the painting on the right. How does each work reflect a particular political point of view?&nbsp;","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"A painting shows the death of a general. He is fallen on the ground and looks skyward. His arms are held by his men, while a medical officer tries to stop his bleeding. The generalâ€™s musket, bayonet, and cartridge box are in front of him. Two men behind him look at the scene, one of them holding a flag. Two groups of men are flanked on either side of the general, looking at him with a despaired look, their hands clasped on their chests. An indigenous man crouches in front of the general, holding a musket and looking at him with a hand on his chin. Dark clouds are in the background, and a battle rages behind them.\n\" height=\"316\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/e0891180a09989b5ff550ae10781b5c3/original.jpg\" width=\"450\" /></p>\n\n<p>LEFT</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"A painting shows soldiers of a firing squad aiming their bayonets in point-blank range at their captives in the dark of the night. A lantern is between the soldiers and the captives. The soldiers carry packs on their backs, have a sword in a sheath around their waist, and are in a dark uniform. Some captives raise their hands and cower, some lie dead, while others cover their faces.\n\" height=\"348\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/7e259a8083792560a8f9ba11e3470def/original.jpg\" width=\"450\" /></p>\n\n<p>RIGHT</p>\n"}]}]